            <title>[OAK-1441] o.a.j.o.api.Tree/Root allows access to hidden nodes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1441</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s possible to access hidden nodes by using the Tree/Root class.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using something like &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;o.a.j.o.a.Root root = ...;
Tree hidden = root.getTree(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/oak:index/test-index/:index&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt;(Tree t : hidden.getChildren()){
   &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.out.println(t);
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;will dump something like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;/oak:index/test-index/:index/value049: { :next = , test = { ... } }
/oak:index/test-index/:index/value009: { :next = value010, test = { ... } }
/oak:index/test-index/:index/value046: { :next = value047, test = { ... } }
/oak:index/test-index/:index/value045: { :next = value046, test = { ... } }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
